                                        <th></th>
                                        <th>Considerations of Fraud and Error when Concluding and Reporting</th>
                                        <th>Yes/No/NA</th>
                                        <th>Reference/Comments</th>
                                    </tr>
                                </thead>
                              <tbody>
                                <tr>
                                  <td>19.</td>
                                  <td >
                                    When the audit committee or equivalent plays an active role in oversight of how management has discharged its responsibilities, auditors are encouraged to seek their views on the adequacy of accounting and control systems in place to prevent and detect fraud and error, the risk of fraud and error, and the competence and integrity of management 
                                  </td>
                                  <td contenteditable="true"></td>
                                  <td contenteditable="true"></td> 
                                </tr>
